oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Snapp family home
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior view of the home owned by Wesley Snapp (1843-1903). Susan Snapp (1845-1929) is standing in the front yard with six of her ten children. Another person is looking from the second floor window. The home was built in 1900 and later burned in the 1930s.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Families
